There is no single "complete text file" for all of EVE Online, as the game consists of over 10GB of data, including textures, models, and audio. However, there are several ways to access all the game's item data, market information, and user settings in text-based formats (YAML, JSON, CSV, or XML). 
Here are the best ways to get EVE Online data files:
1. The Static Data Export (SDE)
This is the most comprehensive file containing all game data, such as items, ships, market groups, and map information. 

    Format: YAML files (contained within a zip file).
    How to get it: The official source is the EVE Developers Resources page.
    Usage: You can use tools like the EVE SDE Database Builder to convert these files into a more usable SQLite or SQL format. 

2. ESI (EVE Swagger Interface) 
This is the official API to fetch live, up-to-date data, such as market prices, character data, or alliance information. 

    Format: JSON (via REST API).
    Usage: Best for active, automated data gathering rather than a one-time file dump. 

3. Third-Party Data Dumps
Many developers provide pre-processed data that is easier to use than the raw SDE.

    Fuzzwork Enterprises: Fuzzmiester provides SQL dumps of the SDE in SQLite format.
    Pyfa/Phobos: A script to pull a full data dump and convert it to JSON. 

4. User Configuration Files
If you are looking for local settings, such as your UI, overview, or overview settings, these are stored in text formats in your app data folders. 

    Path (Windows): C:\Users\Username\AppData\Local\CCP\EVE\ (Note: AppData is a hidden folder).
    Prefs.ini: Contains client settings.
    Overview Settings: Exportable via the in-game overview settings menu as .yaml files. 

5. Log Files
EVE generates text-based logs that can be used for parsing information. 

    Chat Logs: Found in Documents\EVE\logs\Chatlogs.
    Market Logs: Older market data dumps. 

How to Get Specific Game Text Files (Advanced)
If you want to extract specific models, icons, or text strings directly from the game files without downloading the whole SDE, you can use the resfileindex.txt file located in C:\Users\User\Documents\Sharedcache\tq. This allows you to find specific file references and download them from resources.eveonline.com. 





